news.title: Noida authority tell four societies to repair STPs by Feb 15 or OCs will be cancelled
news.para: The developers concerned are Assotech Windsor Court, Skytech Construction Pvt Ltd, Gardenia India Ltd and Futec Shelters Pvt Ltd, and the non-functional STPs they operate are in housing societies in sectors 78, 76, 75 and 78, respectively.

news.title: Pune civic body tell developer to stop project work
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC)’s city engineer, Prashant Waghmare, said, “The development control rules have made it clear that the safety and the security is the responsibility of the developers."

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body using LiDAR technology to survey properties
news.para: Municipal commissioner Abhijit Bangar said the agency, which is carrying out the survey, has been directed to complete the first phase of the work by the end of July this year.

news.title: Kochi Metro phase 1-A extension line to open in April
news.para: More than 90% of the construction works have been completed and it is learnt that the trial run on the track would begin on February 12.

news.title: Fix premium rates for violators of building plans: Madras HC
news.para: ​"Electricity supply may be an essential service for any person, but certainly it shall not be to the violators and it has got to be fixed at the premium rate till the building is brought back in accordance with the plan," a division bench of Justices S Vaidyanathan and D Bharatha Chakravarthy has said.

news.title: Cuttack: Court nod to auction of sham realty firms' assets
news.para: The attached properties of the twin real estate firms are worth around Rs 1.14 crore which includes 18.30 acres of land with a market value of nearly Rs 1.05 crore and nine bank accounts with deposits of Rs 8.87 lakh.

news.title: Nashik realty on fast track in fringes, Adgaon & Pathardi belts lead race
news.para: Sources associated with the real estate sector said Adgaon-Makhmalabad and Pathardi-New Indiranagar were registering a significant growth in terms of getting new projects as compared to other areas on the outskirts of Nashik.

news.title: Activists raise concerns over unmonitored constructions in Pune
news.para: “We have been making demands to authorities to set up teams for keeping a watch on ongoing constructions in each ward. We sought special focus on safety and security of workers. But all these demands have remained on paper,” said labour activist Nitin Pawar.

news.title: Rajkot civic body clears 521 sq meter land on University-Raiya road
news.para: According to RMC, The demolition was done under a special drive planned in ward 9 to remove encroachment and widen the road

news.title: Ahmedabad: 892 units with property tax dues over Rs 1 lakh sealed
news.para: “Between February 1 and 4, we have sealed 892 properties whose pending tax amount exceeded Rs 1 lakh. We have recovered around Rs 15 crore of pending taxes in these four days,” said Jainik Vakil, chairman of AMC’s revenue committee.

news.title: Indore: 20 buyers get possession of plots in Phoenix Township
news.para: “Twenty persons were provided possession of plots in Phoenix Township, for which they had paid years ago,” SDM Anshul Khare said.

news.title: Gurugram: Vipul Lavanya road blocked, court seeks builders' reply in a month
news.para: The land on which 24-metre access road to Vipul Lavanya was built was earlier owned by developer Vipul Ltd, which later sold it to SRV Automotives Pvt Ltd. In December last year, SRV blocked access to the society by installing fences and excavating the road despite the fact the road was part of its approved layout plan, residents claimed.

news.title: Gurugram: BPTP RWA stops essential services, residents protest
news.para: On Thursday, the BPTP Park Life RWA had taken a decision to curtail all these services to the residents who have not paid Common area maintenance (CAM) charges and instructed the facility management to stop entry of all vendors giving services to them, the residents alleged.

news.title: No 'coercive' action to be taken against MGF: Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: Last month, the Gurgaon police filed an FIR against MGF and its directors in the land dispute, following three consecutive orders from the district court.

news.title: NGT restrains Oberoi Realty from creating third-party rights in Worli project
news.para: It has ordered the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA), the State Environment Impact Assessment Authority (SEIAA) Maharashtra and the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board (MPCB) to hold a joint meeting within a month to ensure compliance with the project.
